  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 4</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, <span class=\"text-highlight\">wide-based pan</span> (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chicken thigh fillets</strong> with the <strong>dried&nbsp;</strong><strong>oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, turning once halfway, until golden on both sides</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>mayonnaise</strong> to a bowl with the juice of 1/2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lemon</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>creamy dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098__step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098__step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098__step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098__step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098__step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is golden, reduce the heat to low, add a splash of <strong>water</strong>, cover with a lid and&nbsp;cook for 10-12 min or until it's cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dice the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>diced apple</strong> to a very large bowl with the juice of the remaining <strong>lemon</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: the lemon juice&nbsp;prevents the apple from going brown!</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>sultanas</strong> to a small bowl and cover them with&nbsp;<strong>boiled water </strong>(this plumps them up)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>ciabatta roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into small, bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>ciabatta&nbsp;</strong>to one side of the baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>walnuts</strong> to the other side of the baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until they've darkened slightly in colour and toasted&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1098.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
